Usage: get_nets [-help] [-filter <expr>] [-hierarchical] [-hsc <char>]
                [-nocase] [-quiet] [-regexp] [<patterns> | -of_objects <object_list>]

-help                              # Prints out the command usage
<patterns>                         # Patterns for net names (string, optional)
-filter <expr>                     # Filters the collection with the specified
                                   # expression (string, optional)
-hierarchical                      # Patterns should match hierarchically
                                   # (bool, optional)
-hsc <char>                        # Hierarchical delimiter for pattern.
                                   # (string, optional)
-nocase                            # Pattern matching is not case sensitive
                                   # (bool, optional)
-of_objects <object_list>          # Creates a collection of all nets
                                   # associated with the specified cells, pins,
                                   # or ports (string, optional)
-quiet                             # Suppresses all error and warning messages
                                   # generated when the get_nets command is run
                                   # (bool, optional)
-regexp                            # Treats the specified patterns as a regular
                                   # expression patterns (bool, optional)